============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Monetarism
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Inflation caused primarily by excessive money supply growth
Formula:    MV = PQ
Economist:  Milton Friedman
Example:    Fed raising interest rates to control money supply and inflation

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Alzheimer's
Type:        Neurological
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Aging/genetics
Symptoms:    Memory loss, confusion
Treatment:   No cure; slowing medications
Deaths/yr:   0.12M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1906

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

Disease:     Smallpox
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Variola
Transmission:Respiratory, contact
Symptoms:    Pockmarks, fever
Treatment:   Eradicated (1980)
Deaths/yr:   EradicatedM
Vaccine:     Yes
Discovered:  Antiquity

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Schwarzschild Radius
Formula: r_s = 2GM/c²
Note:    Event horizon radius of a black hole

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Speed of Light
Formula: c = 299,792,458 m/s in vacuum
Note:    Foundation of special relativity; universal speed limit

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   2nd Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔS ≥ 0
Note:    Entropy always increases in isolated systems

Domain:  Astronomy
Topic:   Hubble's Law
Formula: v = H₀ × d
Note:    Universe is expanding; galaxies recede from us

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Cell Theory
Formula: All life is made of cells arising from pre-existing cells
Note:    Foundation of modern biology

